Now I can read VGA text memory! I can see "SeaBIOS (version 1.16.3-debian-1.16.3-2)", "Booting from Hard Disk...", "Starting MS-DOS...". The boot is progressing. Let me wait longer for Windows to start.

{
  "analysis": "VGA text memory readable! Shows: 'SeaBIOS (version 1.16.3-debian-1.16.3-2)', 'Booting from Hard Disk...', 'Starting MS-DOS...'. Boot is in progress after 15s. Need to wait longer for DOS to fully load and Windows to start.",
  "plan": "Wait 30 more seconds and read VGA text memory again to check if Windows has started or if there's an error.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "sleep 30 && echo 'xp /2000xb 0xb8000' | socat - UNIX-CONNECT:/tmp/qemu-monitor.sock 2>&1 | grep -v '^00000000000b8' | head -5; echo '---'; echo 'xp /2000xb 0xb8000' | socat - UNIX-CONNECT:/tmp/qemu-monitor.sock 2>&1 | python3 -c "
import sys
data = sys.stdin.read()
lines = [l for l in data.split('\n') if ':' in l and '0x' in l]
chars = []
for line in lines:
    parts = line.split(':', 1)
    if len(parts) >= 2:
        for h in parts[1].strip().split():
            if h.startswith('0x'):
                chars.append(int(h, 16))
for row in range(25):
    line = ''
    for col in range(80):
        idx = (row * 80 + col) * 2
        if idx < len(chars):
            ch = chars[idx]
            line += chr(ch) if 32 <= ch < 127 else '.'
    if line.strip('.'):
        print(f'{row:2d}: {line.rstrip()}')
"
",
      "duration": 40.0
    }
  ],
  "task_complete": false
}
